MONDAY TO THURSDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND
MARITIME AGENCY AT 092300 UTC
ON MONDAY EVENING HIGH PRESSURE CENTRED OVER SE BISCAY
1034 WITH A RIDGE EXTENDING N ACROSS MUCH OF THE BRITISH
ISLES AND N SEA. THROUGH THE PERIOD THE HIGH DRIFTS E
ACROSS THE NEAR CONTINENT BLDN A LITTLE TO LIE OVER
CENTRAL GERMANY AROUND 1038 BY MIDDAY ON THURSDAY.
RIDGE CONDITIONS WILL BE MAINTAINED ACROSS MUCH OF THE
BRITISH ISLES AND THE N SEA THROUGH THIS PERIOD. ATLANTIC
LOWS AND ASSOCIATED ACTIVE FRONTAL TROUGHS WILL BE MAINLY
RESTRICTED TO SEA AREAS N AND W OF SCOTLAND ALTHOUGH A
WKN FRONTAL TROUGH IS EXP TO AFFECT THE N OF THE BRITISH
ISLES THROUGH TUESDAY AND WEDNESDAY. RISK OF GALES IN
SHANNON ON MONDAY EVENING AND TUESDAY MORNING THEN AGAIN
LATER WEDNESDAY INTO THURSDAY. THROUGH THE PERIOD OCNL
STRG WINDS MAY AFFECT OTHER SEA AREAS NEAR IRELAND AND
